Help Type: command
Command: spinedigest find

Purpose:
  Find archive objects by deterministic keyword search.

Usage:
  spinedigest find <archive.sdpub> <query> --type <node|summary|fragment> [--match <any|all>] [--chapter <ids>] [--order <doc-asc|doc-desc>] [--limit <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--json]

Contract:
  - Mutates: no.
  - LLM: no.
  - Searches: summaries, graph node summaries, or source fragments depending on `--type`.
  - Query: split on whitespace into keywords.
  - Match: default `--match any` returns objects containing at least one keyword and ranks stronger matches first.
  - Strict match: `--match all` requires every keyword to appear inside the same returned object.
  - Scope: `--chapter 12` or `--chapter 11,12` limits results to chapters.
  - Search lens: `--type` is required.
  - Types: `--type node` searches topology / LLM Wiki structure, `--type summary` searches quick overview text, and `--type fragment` searches original source wording.
  - Order: `doc-asc` or `doc-desc`; default `doc-asc`.
  - Pagination: default `--limit 20`; pass returned `nextCursor` back with `--cursor`.
  - Matching: case-insensitive substring matching, with no semantic expansion, stemming, fuzzy matching, or vector search.
  - JSON: yes.

Use `grep` instead when the query must be treated as one exact continuous text phrase.

Examples:
  spinedigest find book.sdpub "朱元璋 濠州 和州 集庆 应天 洪都 鄱阳湖" --type node --json
  spinedigest find book.sdpub "鄱阳湖" --type summary --json
  spinedigest find book.sdpub "亲自来到洪都" --type fragment --json
  spinedigest find book.sdpub "朱元璋 亲自 来到" --type fragment --match all --json
  spinedigest find book.sdpub "张定边" --chapter 12 --type node --limit 10 --json
